article.description: Arkansas State rolls past Central Arkansas 67-49
article.headline: Arkansas State rolls past Central Arkansas 67-49
article.linkText: Arkansas State rolls past Central Arkansas 67-49
article.story:
CONWAY, Ark. --  Anthony Livingston made 8 of 13 from the floor and finished with 20 points to lead Arkansas State to a 67-49 win over Central Arkansas on Monday night.

Arkansas State held a slim 29-28 halftime advantage but gradually pulled away in the second half and was ahead 46-36 midway through the final period. Central Arkansas' Mike Martin made two free throws, nailed a 3-pointer and followed with a steal and a layup, and Otas Iyekekpolor made a free throw to close to 52-44 with 7:00 remaining.

Cameron Golden answered with a 3-pointer that led to a 9-0 run and a 61-44 lead with 3:19 left.

Golden, who made 4 of 10 from beyond the arc, had 14 points and Nouhoum Boucoum added 12 for Arkansas State (1-2).

Martin nailed 3 of 4 from long range and had 13 points and Howard chipped in 10 for the Bears (0-7).
